One of the rules of the chip shot is that before doing it, take a short and quick look at how the goalkeeper is guarding and how far he is from the goal, and then shoot so that you know how much power and height you should give to the ball.
If an attacker makes these calculations before shooting, he can make a better decision, maybe not even needing a chip shot and can shot the ball through the goalkeeper's side or between his legs 🤷‍♂️
